{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17636684","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17636684"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:32:02+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:32:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17600"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17600","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17600"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10314"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75474"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10314","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10314"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17600"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60984"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5671"},{"type":"tags","id":"5764"},{"type":"tags","id":"7822"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24114"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24180"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75474","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75474"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EMedical research ethics requires careful consideration of participant autonomy and protection. Before enrolling participants in research studies, investigators must obtain proper consent.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the essential core requirements for valid informed consent in medical research?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Disclosure of risks and benefits, capacity to understand, voluntary participation","Written documentation with witness signature","Ethics committee approval","Translator availability and a clear cooling off period","Verbal consent process with clear payment disclosure"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EValid informed consent requires three essential elements: \u003Cstrong\u003Edisclosure of risks and benefits, capacity to understand,\u003C/strong\u003E and\u003Cstrong\u003E voluntary participation\u003C/strong\u003E. The researcher must provide comprehensive information about the study, ensure the participant can understand and process this information, and confirm participation is free from coercion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Ewritten documentation with witness signatures\u003C/strong\u003E may be helpful, they are not essential requirements for consent; additionally written documentation is not valid if the consent process does not also meet the three essential elements of consent outlined above.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEthics committee approval\u003C/strong\u003E is a separate process from individual consent.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETranslator availability, payment disclosure and cooling-off periods\u003C/strong\u003E are procedural considerations to gaining informed consent rather than core requirements of informed consent.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdditional considerations include cultural sensitivity, appropriate documentation, and special protections for vulnerable populations. The consent process should be ongoing throughout the research study.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Research participants must provide informed consent before participating in medical research.","Valid informed consent requires disclosure of risks and benefits, capacity to understand, and voluntary participation without coercion.","Vulnerable populations require additional safeguards to ensure ethical research participation."],"references":["Manti S, Licari A. How to obtain informed consent for research. Breathe (Sheff). 2018 Jun;14(2):145-152. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC5980471/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60984"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17600"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60984","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60984"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T20:58:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-30T00:54:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10314"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75474"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4948","